text:
Computer Science student at BYU-Idaho (certificates in Computer Programming & Machine Learning; minor in Music) seeking a software development internship.

zvolmer@byui.edu | 509-964-4009 | LinkedIn | GitHub



Computer Science student at BYU-Idaho (certificates in Computer Programming & Machine Learning; minor in Music) seeking a software development internship.


Strong knowledge of Python and C#. Moderate knowledge of SQL, Pandas, HTML, and CSS. Beginner knowledge of JavaScript, TypeScript, React Native and Unity. Teamwork, leadership, critical thinking and problem solving.



React Native app group project. Website for band. Unity Target Shooter Game.




September 2024 - Present Brigham Young University - Idaho

Bachelors; Computer Science
Current GPA: 3.6

September 2022 - June 2024 Columbia Basin College

Associate; Arts and Sciences
GPA: 3.67











Ongoing React Native app group project.
Ongoing Website for band.
Ongoing Unity Target Shooter Game.




January 2020 - Present (self-employed) - Musician, Richland, WA

Founded and managed a band - handled scheduling, booking, and logistics for rehearsals, recording sessions, and live concerts. Collaborated closely with a recording engineer to record two full-length albums and one EP.
Mixed and mastered one album; earned professional certification in Pro Tools to improve production quality and workflow.
Executed marketing and distribution strategies generating 50,000+ streams and ~200 CD sales.

January 2022 - December 2025 Jamba - Shift Lead, Richland, WA

Operated register and managed customer transactions with precision and efficiency.
Prepared smoothies and food items to uphold brand standards during peak hours.
Provided leadership by delegating tasks and supporting team workflow.
Maintained a clean and safe work environment through routine cleaning and equipment upkeep.

January 2024 - December 2024 Temp-Co Heating - HVAC Assistant, St. George, Utah

Shadowed lead technicians in balancing air-conditioning units to optimize airflow and system performance.
Accurately labeled piping, ductwork, and system components on construction sites to support installation and future maintenance.
